<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10096d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10096d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10096d"> 96(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> value declared / tax</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Depuis la mort de Henri IV jusqu&apos;en l&apos;ann&eacute;e 1627, les habitants de certaines villes, et notamment de Paris, s&apos;&eacute;taient arrog&eacute; le droit de taxer eux-m&ecirc;mes le port des lettres qui leur &eacute;taient adress&eacute;es, &ldquo;au lieu d&apos;acquitter simplement <mark>la taxe que leur fixait</mark> l&apos;administration, agissant en vertu des pouvoirs conf&eacute;r&eacute;s par l&apos;&eacute;dit de mai 1597.&rdquo; Le nouveau directeur et intendant des Postes r&eacute;solut de faire cesser cet abus qui compromettait gravement les int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts du tr&eacute;sor royal. A la date du 16 octobre 1627, il publia un r&egrave;glement ordonnant &agrave; tout destinataire &ldquo;de lettres et de paquets&rdquo; de payer &ldquo;sans contestation ni r&eacute;plique&rdquo; les sommes que les agents de l&apos;intendance leur r&eacute;clameraient pour port desdits envois. <font color="green">[From Henry IV&apos;s death until 1627, the inhabitants of certain cities, notably Paris, had themselves assumed the right to tax the transportation of letters that were addressed to them &ldquo;instead of simply paying the tax set by the administration, acting under the powers granted by the edict of May 1597&rdquo;. The new director and intendant of the Post resolved to put an end to this abuse that seriously compromised the interests of the Royal Treasury. On 16 October 1627 he published a ruling commanding all recipients &ldquo;of letters and packages&rdquo; to pay &ldquo;without dispute or rejoinder&rdquo; the amount which the agents of the commissariat demanded from them for the aforementioned shipments.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 164-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
